body:
We all know, when we subscribe to route params or query params, we must unsubscribe in onDestroy method to avoid memory leak. For example

```javascript
ngOnInit(): void {
        this.paramsSubscription = this.route.params.subscribe((param: any) => {
                console.log(params['type']);
        });
}

ngOnDestroy(): void {
        this.paramsSubscription.unsubscribe();
}
```

But I needed to Subscribe to both **route params and query params at the same time**, so did the following
```javascript
this.obsCombined = Observable.combineLatest(this.route.params, this.route.queryParams, (params, qparams) => ({params, qparams}));
        this.obsCombined.subscribe(ap => {
            console.log(ap.params['type']);
            console.log(ap.qparams['page']);
});
```

So, my question is, **do I need to unsubscribe, if yes then how do I unsubscribe** with "Observable.combineLatest ()" ?
I am also open to suggestions.
Note: query params are optional, i.e.
```javascript
this.router.navigate([type]);
this.router.navigate([type], {queryParams: {page: pageNo}});
```
